The paper deals with approximation algorithms for the minimum cost homomorphism problem, which is a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem involves graphs and digraphs, which are topics in computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses dichotomy classifications, which are related to graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper mentions constant factor approximation algorithms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
